When is the error triggered?
- When accessing the array element with an invalid index: at data[idx] if idx < 0 or idx >= data.length.

 How would you check this?
- Option A (bounds check):
  if (idx < 0 || idx >= data.length) {
      System.out.println("Out of Bounds");
  } else {
      System.out.println("Value: " + data[idx]);
  }
- Option B (try/catch demonstration):
  try {
      System.out.println("Value: " + data[idx]); // triggers if index is invalid
  } catch (ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException e) {
      System.out.println("Out of Bounds");
  }
